{
  "stem": "9730.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And of course, you could see the German defenses crumbling at that point.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But, you know, they were still, of course-- some of them were diehards, and they just didn't want to-- to give up.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They also-- the thing that invariably came up in their-- in their interrogation was that-- that they, the Germans, were working on secret weapons that would allow them to win-- to still win the war.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And of course, some of this was-- was to some-- at one point, when we kept hearing those stories, we couldn't know for sure because there were, in fact, the V-1s and V-2s, and we didn't know what else they might have up their sleeves.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we-- we learned to-- not to pooh-pooh these things.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But quite obviously, they had been fed a lot of propaganda about the so-called secret weapon.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But I also found out for the first time about jet fighters, you know, which-- which they had in those days.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And so we didn't know really what-- what else might show up.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, once we left Frankfurt and-- we-- we were called to the border area between Germany and Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were-- we were to link up with the Russians, who were coming through Czechoslovakia, you know, in the opposite direction.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so I remember getting to a town called Eleonorenhain in-- which was in the so-called Sudeten area, which was the border between Germany and-- and Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And in those towns, the populace was mostly Sudeten Germans rather than Czechs.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we were at first mired in the mud for-- for a number of days in this town of Eleonorenhain.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We couldn't advance because of incessant rains.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
